<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="870" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.711/3</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Acting Secretary of State to the Consul General at
                                Rotterdam</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LS1"><hi rend="italic">Listoe</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-23">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1914</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Telegraph fully whether your office is transmitting commercial
                            correspondence to and from Germany or other country or whether
                            arrangements being made to that end. If so explain nature and number of
                            telegrams, whether from Americans or foreigners and authority for
                            transmitting. Answer.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>